dn’t skip any conditions and could utilize an assertion like `assertThat(unmapped).isIn(true, false)`. That feels a bit silly to me, though. Maybe I should consider asserting the file content in cases where the value returns false? It's definitely worth exploring further!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Editing and building**\\n\\nOkay, so I’m thinking about editing the build and writing tests. I want to make sure everything is up to spec. Writing tests is crucial for ensuring that the code works as intended. I need to focus on what areas to test and if there are any specific features that require more attention. So, let’s dive in and get this organized, prioritizing what needs to be done first. I’m eager to get everything flowing smoothly!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NqeGzlMb0cs7WkfYt2629wyH|fc_0f9710af214907270169f4d3964e148194abfbfa1bcb50f7ae", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/h2/MemoryUnmapperTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage h2;\n\nimport org.h2.util.MemoryUnmapper;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.nio.ByteBuffer;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatCode;\n\npublic class MemoryUnmapperTest {\n    @Test\n    void unmapRejectsHeapBuffersWithoutThrowing() {\n        ByteBuffer buffer = ByteBuffer.allocate(16);\n\n        boolean unmapped = MemoryUnmapper.unmap(buffer);\n\n        assertThat(unmapped).isFalse();\n        assertThat(buffer.capacity()).isEqualTo(16);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void unmapAttemptsToCleanDirectBuffers() {\n        ByteBuffer buffer = ByteBuffer.allocateDirect(16);\n        buffer.putInt(42);\n\n        assertThatCode(() -> MemoryUnmapper.unmap(buffer)).doesNotThrowAnyException();\n    }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/h2/MemoryUnmapperTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage h2;\\n\\nimport org.h2.util.MemoryUnmapper;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport java.nio.ByteBuffer;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatCode;\\n\\npublic class MemoryUnmapperTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void unmapRejectsHeapBuffersWithoutThrowing() {\\n        ByteBuffer buffer = ByteBuffer.allocate(16);\\n\\n        boolean unmapped = MemoryUnmapper.unmap(buffer);\\n\\n        assertThat(unmapped).isFalse();\\n        assertThat(buffer.capacity()).isEqualTo(16);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void unmapAttemptsToCleanDirectBuffers() {\\n        ByteBuffer buffer = ByteBuffer.allocateDirect(16);\\n        buffer.putInt(42);\\n\\n        assertThatCode(() -> MemoryUnmapper.unmap(buffer)).doesNotThrowAnyException();\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1285, "output": 2159, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28532, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777652601837, "responseId": "resp_0f9710af214907270169f4d37a8a4c8194965dd3a92d606a63"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_NqeGzlMb0cs7WkfYt2629wyH|fc_0f9710af214907270169f4d3964e148194abfbfa1bcb50f7ae", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 984 bytes to tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/h2/MemoryUnmapperTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777652631349}]}
